description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for a new challenge in the New Year? Could you bring your Mental healthcare experience to support patients with EUPD in the ASSIST service at Berkshire NHS Foundation Trust?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;ASSIST is a newly established psychologically informed team, providing a collaborative and compassionate service to people with EUPD. &lt;strong&gt;If you have always wanted to offer real choice and a positive, consistent experience to patients&lt;/strong&gt; in a time measured and effective way, then we would love to hear from you.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Berkshire NHS Foundation Trust are rated &lt;strong&gt;‘Outstanding’ in their most recent CQC report&lt;/strong&gt; as well as being recognised as a &lt;strong&gt;Global Digital Exemplar&lt;/strong&gt;. In this role you will be located in and working across an area with all the benefits of country living with the convenience of big city life.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Who are we looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Senior Mental Health Practitioner to join the ASSIST team in a long-term placement- 6 months to 14 months dependant on the ideal candidate’s availability. ASSIST is a service designed to provide intensive and time limited psycho-social interventions for residents of Berkshire, who may have or meet the diagnosis for emotionally Unstable Personality Disorder (EUPD). &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The Trust’s overall objective is to provide the best patient care, bridging to treatments within the EUPD pathway. This in turn will reduce hospital admissions and length of stay.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;To apply for this post, you will have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree level Professional qualification – Nurse, OT, Social worker Clinical/counselling psychologist and current professional registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years’ post-qualification experience of working with adults with mental health problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 years’ experience of working with EUPD in the Community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;What will be your main responsibilities?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing intensive 1:1 and group support to a small number of people who have a diagnosis of EUPD as part of a team approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide practical and psychological interventions as part of a person-centred plan of care and involve the wider support network and treatment teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver Care that is responsive and work collaboratively with other teams to manage risk in a positive and inclusive way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervision of junior staff operating within a multidisciplinary team (MDT).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advocate on behalf of and link with other services to ensure there is a clear transition between services and primary care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As part of the MDT, develop psychological formulations for individual patients that contribute towards the overall assessment of their care needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaboratively establish individual patient’s goals towards recovery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the assessment and identification of specific psychological interventions including group and individual modalities, based on the patient’s assessment/formulation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that Risk management and contingency planning is in line with the Trust’s policy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Placing people at the heart of the NHS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Who are we? Well … If a hospital cannot supply staff on a ward or area, due to increased demand, sickness, or common staff shortages, they need to call upon Bank staff. NHS Professionals works with trusts to develop ‘bank’ of highly skilled workers who want to work flexibly with the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registering with NHS Professionals&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value your skills, dedication, and commitment in supporting your local Trust and the NHS. We believe together we continue to deliver world-class healthcare service to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By joining us you can bring your Mental Health expertise in supporting and providing exceptional patient care and in return you can benefit from several attractive incentives:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive Pay Rates - work this week, get paid next week!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First choice of shifts at your Trust – Access to shifts before they are available to agency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working to suit your lifestyle – Take control of when you want to work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build holiday allowance for every shift you work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Book and manage your shifts on the go – Access shifts anywhere, anytime online or through your smartphone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support when you need it – 24/7 365 days – Call us anytime&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply today for various flexible shifts and long-term placement opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
